Write bridge beats. The woven story has adjacent scenes that share no characters,
place, or object — the cut between them would jar. For each gap below, write ONE
short structural beat that carries the reader across: a transition, a passage of
time, a change of place. Bridges serve the story's shape, not any dilemma — they
must not advance, reveal, or decide anything dramatic.

VISION: {{ vision.genre }}, {{ vision.tone }}.

GAPS:
{% for gap in gaps %}
- gap {{ gap.index }}:
  from: {{ gap.src.id }} — {{ gap.src.summary }} (entities: {{ gap.src.entities | join(", ") }})
  to:   {{ gap.dst.id }} — {{ gap.dst.summary }} (entities: {{ gap.dst.entities | join(", ") }})
{% endfor %}

REQUIREMENTS:
- Exactly one bridge per gap, keyed by its gap number.
- 1-2 sentence summary, present tense, matching the tone.
- Beat ids: beat:slug. List the entities the bridge touches (ideally one from each
  side of the gap).
